It appears your AWS Organizations delegation policy has a JSON syntax error. Looking at your policy, I can see a few potential issues:
In the "Fully_manage_backup_policies" statement, you're using "RESOURCE_CONTROL_POLICY" in the condition, but this might not be a valid policy type for AWS Organizations. The standard policy types include SERVICE_CONTROL_POLICY, TAG_POLICY, BACKUP_POLICY, AISERVICES_OPT_OUT_POLICY, and others.
There might be trailing commas or formatting issues that are causing the JSON validation to fail.
To resolve this issue, I recommend the following steps:
Copy your policy JSON
Convert or validate it using the IAM policy editor:
Go to the IAM console
Choose "Policies"
Click "Create policy"
Select the "JSON" tab
Paste your policy
The editor will highlight any syntax errors
Fix the identified errors
Once the policy validates correctly in the IAM editor, copy it back to the Organizations delegation policy creation page
Common JSON syntax errors include:
Extra or missing commas
Unmatched brackets or braces
Invalid policy types or actions
Incorrect formatting of ARNs
After correcting any syntax issues, try creating the delegation policy again. If you continue to have issues, you might need to verify that the policy types and actions you're using are supported for delegation in AWS Organizations.
Sources
Create a resource-based delegation policy with AWS Organizations - AWS Organizations
